Visited Oh La La this evening and had a mixed dining experience. We ordered the Pepperoni Pizza, Fish and Chips, and Cappuccinos.

The Pepperoni Pizza was overly salty, with a thin and hard base. While it was edible, the texture made it less enjoyable.

The Fish and Chips was initially served with the fish raw in the center. Although the staff apologized and replaced it, the second serving, while cooked, was unseasoned, both in the fish and the batter. The large size of the fish fillet seems to contribute to the cooking issues, as it makes it challenging to prepare evenly.

The Cappuccinos were a disappointment, arriving lukewarm and lacking the comforting warmth one would expect.

The real highlight of the evening, however, was the in-house parrot, which provided some unexpected entertainment by flying to a guest's table and stealing their fish!  ðŸ¤£ðŸ¤£

While the setting is remarkable, the food quality needs significant improvement to encourage repeat visits. A better focus on seasoning, preparation, and attention to detail in serving could elevate the overall dining experience.
